4:"Sets the per-query cache duration.  The value is specified in seconds.  0 or blank mean no per-query caching.  Per-query caching caches individual database queries, and must be specified on a per-query basis (see the API references for more info).  Note: Query caching also requires PHP\'s DBA extension.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:304:"Sets the per-query cache duration.  The value is specified in seconds.  0 or blank mean no per-query caching.  Per-query caching caches individual database queries, and must be specified on a per-query basis (see the API references for more info).  Note: Query caching also requires PHP\'s DBA extension.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:39:"inc/app/usradm/forms/cache/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:4:"Site";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:4:"Site";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:13:"Site Settings";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:13:"Site Settings";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:39:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/index.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:20:"Site settings saved.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:20:"Site settings saved.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:39:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/index.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:21:"Sitellite HTTP Header";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:21:"Sitellite HTTP Header";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:128:"Specifies whether or not to use persistent connections when connecting to your database.  Usually, it is best to leave this off.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:128:"Specifies whether or not to use persistent connections when connecting to your database.  Usually, it is best to leave this off.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:68:"Specifies whether to enable Jabber message forwarding and receiving.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:68:"Specifies whether to enable Jabber message forwarding and receiving.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:8:"Statuses";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:8:"Statuses";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:36:"inc/app/usradm/boxes/index/index.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:11:"System Name";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:11:"System Name";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/boxes/browse/_resources.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:4:"Team";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:4:"Team";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:38:"inc/app/usradm/boxes/browse/_users.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:5:"Teams";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:5:"Teams";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:36:"inc/app/usradm/boxes/index/index.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:11:"Teams found";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:11:"Teams found";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:38:"inc/app/usradm/boxes/browse/_teams.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:88:"The Jabber server to check for incoming instant messages.  This must be a Jabber server.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:88:"The Jabber server to check for incoming instant messages.  This must be a Jabber server.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:130:"The domain name of the site, used by the scheduler to refer to in command-line mode where no domain is used in the script request.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:130:"The domain name of the site, used by the scheduler to refer to in command-line mode where no domain is used in the script request.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:224:"The email server to check for incoming email.  This must be a POP3 email server.  Ordinarily, simply setting up a dedicated email account for Sitellite on your existing mail server is sufficient to enable this functionality.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:224:"The email server to check for incoming email.  This must be a POP3 email server.  Ordinarily, simply setting up a dedicated email account for Sitellite on your existing mail server is sufficient to enable this functionality.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:271:"The full directory path to the web site directory.  Note: This is the filesystem path and not the web-visible path.  If set to empty, the value will be auto-discovered.  Please note that if the 'Use Document Root' setting above is set to 'No', this value will be ignored.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:271:"The full directory path to the web site directory.  Note: This is the filesystem path and not the web-visible path.  If set to empty, the value will be auto-discovered.  Please note that if the 'Use Document Root' setting above is set to 'No', this value will be ignored.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:27:"The item has been restored.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:27:"The item has been restored.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:34:"inc/app/usradm/conf/properties.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:28:"The items have been deleted.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:28:"The items have been deleted.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:34:"inc/app/usradm/conf/properties.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:259:"The location to store proxy cache 'tag' files, which are empty files that are created and updated on creation and re-creation of a mod:proxy cached page.  These help determine whether or not to regenerate the file or send the appropriate HTTP headers instead.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:259:"The location to store proxy cache 'tag' files, which are empty files that are created and updated on creation and re-creation of a mod:proxy cached page.  These help determine whether or not to regenerate the file or send the appropriate HTTP headers instead.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:39:"inc/app/usradm/forms/cache/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:461:"The location to store the page-level cache.  It may be a directory name (ie. cache/pages), mod:proxy, which will generates the proper HTTP headers for a proxy/cache server to provide the caching, bdb:path/to/page_store.db, which uses the Berkeley DB software to store the cached pages, or memcache:server:port, which uses Memcached to store the cached pages.  Note: Berkeley DB stores require PHP's DBA extension and Memcached requires PHP's Memcache extension.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:461:"The location to store the page-level cache.  It may be a directory name (ie. cache/pages), mod:proxy, which will generates the proper HTTP headers for a proxy/cache server to provide the caching, bdb:path/to/page_store.db, which uses the Berkeley DB software to store the cached pages, or memcache:server:port, which uses Memcached to store the cached pages.  Note: Berkeley DB stores require PHP's DBA extension and Memcached requires PHP's Memcache extension.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:39:"inc/app/usradm/forms/cache/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:203:"The location to store the per-query cache.  It may be any valid directory name.  In this directory, a few Berkeley DB files will be created, one called query_store.db and one for each query being cached.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:203:"The location to store the per-query cache.  It may be any valid directory name.  In this directory, a few Berkeley DB files will be created, one called query_store.db and one for each query being cached.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:39:"inc/app/usradm/forms/cache/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:136:"The method of determining which language to use for each visitor.  See saf.I18n::negotiate() in the API references for more information.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:136:"The method of determining which language to use for each visitor.  See saf.I18n::negotiate() in the API references for more information.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:102:"The name of the database host server.  If it is the same as the web server, often 'localhost' is fine.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:102:"The name of the database host server.  If it is the same as the web server, often 'localhost' is fine.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:49:"The name of your database on the database server.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:49:"The name of your database on the database server.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:66:"The password to access the Jabber account designated to Sitellite.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:66:"The password to access the Jabber account designated to Sitellite.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:65:"The password to access the email account designated to Sitellite.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:65:"The password to access the email account designated to Sitellite.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:78:"The password you must supply to the database server in order to connect to it.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:78:"The password you must supply to the database server in order to connect to it.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:63:"The port of the Jabber server.  The default is usually correct.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:63:"The port of the Jabber server.  The default is usually correct.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:66:"The port of the POP3 mail server.  The default is usually correct.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:66:"The port of the POP3 mail server.  The default is usually correct.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:66:"The username to access the Jabber account designated to Sitellite.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:66:"The username to access the Jabber account designated to Sitellite.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:65:"The username to access the email account designated to Sitellite.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:65:"The username to access the email account designated to Sitellite.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:78:"The username you must supply to the database server in order to connect to it.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:78:"The username you must supply to the database server in order to connect to it.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:211:"This allows Web Files downloads to be served directly by the web server, which is more efficient than serving through PHP. Please note that some web server configuration changes may be required for this setting.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:211:"This allows Web Files downloads to be served directly by the web server, which is more efficient than serving through PHP. Please note that some web server configuration changes may be required for this setting.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:241:"This determines whether Sitellite will send an 'X-Powered-By: Sitellite' HTTP header with page requests.  The default is 'Yes', which shouldn't be a problem, but some may prefer to turn it off as one extra security-through-obscurity measure.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:241:"This determines whether Sitellite will send an 'X-Powered-By: Sitellite' HTTP header with page requests.  The default is 'Yes', which shouldn't be a problem, but some may prefer to turn it off as one extra security-through-obscurity measure.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:105:"This is the default request handler for when no specific request is made (ie. a request for / or /index).";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:105:"This is the default request handler for when no specific request is made (ie. a request for / or /index).";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:232:"This is the default template theme used ot render pages.  By using this setting, you can add your own template themes, install multiple themes in the same Sitellite installation, by adding sets instead of changing the existing ones.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:232:"This is the default template theme used ot render pages.  By using this setting, you can add your own template themes, install multiple themes in the same Sitellite installation, by adding sets instead of changing the existing ones.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:156:"This is the email address used by Sitellite to send and receive messages emails.  It is the email address recipients will see in the 'From' field of emails.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:156:"This is the email address used by Sitellite to send and receive messages emails.  It is the email address recipients will see in the 'From' field of emails.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:71:"This is the name of the error handler, when an invalid request is made.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:71:"This is the name of the error handler, when an invalid request is made.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:48:"This is the type of the default request handler.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:48:"This is the type of the default request handler.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:38:"This is the type of the error handler.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:38:"This is the type of the error handler.";s:6:"params";b:0;s:4:"file";s:42:"inc/app/usradm/forms/settings/settings.php";s:4:"line";b:0;}s:297:"This sets the default app to look in for boxes, forms, settings, etc.  The default 'webapp' is where you can place your custom code for a single web site.  However, if you are looking to create reusable apps, it is best to create a new app directory structure and not use the default in that case.";a:4:{s:6:"string";s:297:"This sets the default app to look in for boxes, forms, settings, etc.  The default 'webapp' is where you can place your custom code for a